(598, '_transient_wdpun_project_details_679182', '<p>Jealous of those fancy schmancy animated widgets in Facebook and Twitter that constantly scroll the site''s latest info to users?    Well now you can add your own slick animated version to your site with the ''Live Stream Widget''!\nWhat does it do?\nOnce activated, this plugin makes a new widget available that you can add to any sidebar.</p>\n<p><a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/widget1.png"></a></p>\n<p><strong>Features include:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Show an <strong>animated</strong> loop of latest posts and comments</li>\n<li>On Multisite, choose to show content from across the entire network</li>\n<li>Works well with all themes</li>\n<li>Choose height of widget</li>\n<li>Select how many items to show in the loop</li>\n<li>Option to display user avatars</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>To work its magic on Multisite networks, this plugin requires the <a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/project/post-indexer/">Post Indexer</a> and <a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/project/comment-indexer/">Comment Indexer</a> plugins. </strong></p>\n<p><strong>For single WordPress installations, simply activate the plugin and insert the Live Stream Widget into any widgetized area of your &hellip;</strong></p>\n', 'no'),
